            . I live in Rochester-row, Westminster-bridge. The prisoner lodged with me about thirteen weeks - he brought a plough to my house, about a fortnight before he was taken; he said he brought it because he took one from me and pawned it, and brought that instead - he said he went into Forum-street, Berkeley-square, to borrow it for me - I said it was not so good as mine; I gave it to Hopkins.</p>
